6) genetically modified products (hereinafter referred to as GM products) mean products that contain, consist of, or are produced from one or more genetically modified organisms and are intended to be placed on the market;
7) GM products as feed mean feed that contains, consists of, or is produced from one or more genetically modified organisms;
8) GM products as food mean food that contains, consists of, or is produced from one or more genetically modified organisms;
9) a genetically modified source (hereinafter referred to as a GM source) means a line of genetically modified plants, animals, fungi, or microorganisms that contains:
a) specific genetic modification with a particular localization in its genome carried out by methods of genetic engineering; or
b) more than one genetic modification that was carried out by methods of genetic engineering and produced by:
crossing simple GM sources, each containing already existing modifications; or
repeated genetic modification of an existing GM source; or simultaneous introduction of several genes or traits;
10) a genetically modified organism (hereinafter referred to as GMO) means any organism, other than human, in which the genetic material was deliberately modified by transferring an exogenous nucleic acid into the recipient organism’s genome in a way that does not occur naturally through crossing and/or natural recombination;
